save_RESTR_PARAMETER_CLASS

    _definition.id                RESTR_PARAMETER_CLASS
    _definition.scope             Category
    _definition.class             Loop
    _definition.update            2014-06-29
    _description.text
;
      This restraint, which will normally be used to restrain
      the total occupancy of an atom site, can be used to
      restrain the value of
      SUM(over the specified atoms){\PARAMETER*COEFFICIENT\}
      where PARAMETER will usually be the value of the occupancy
      (but other allowed quantities such as x, y and z can be
      specified in the enumeration) and COEFFICIENT is a user-defined
      number with a default value of 1.0.
      The restraint requires two loops, the first defines the
      atoms in each sum (class) and the second describes the
      properties of the class.
;
    _name.category_id             CIF_RESTR_HEAD
    _name.object_id               RESTR_PARAMETER_CLASS
    _category_key.name            '_restr_parameter_class.class_id'

    _description_example.case
;
        loop_
          _restr_parameter_class.class_id
          _restr_parameter_class.parameter_type
          _restr_parameter_class.target
          _restr_parameter_class.target_weight_param
          _restr_parameter_class.details
             1 occupancy   0.8  0.01   'total occupation is 0.8'
             2 occupancy   1.0  0.001  'total occupation is 1.0'
             3 occupancy   2.0  0.01   'total charge is 2.0'
             4 position_y  0.5  0.002  'keep close to pseudo-mirror plane'
             5 position_x  0    0.01   'correlate position of O3 and O4'
;
    _description_example.detail
;
      Example 1. This example gives the properties of the five classes given
      as examples in the RESTR_PARAMETER category.

      *.class_id is the category key and values must match a value of
      _restr_parameter.class_id in the RESTR_PARAMETER category.

      *.parameter_type indicates the atomic parameter that is restrained.

      *.target is the target value for the sum of the product of
      _restr_parameter.atom_coefficient and the value of the
      _restr_parameter_class.parameter_type for the atom.

      *.target_weight_param gives the expectation value of the difference
      between the target and the refined value of sum(coefficient*parameter).

      *.details gives a description of the restraint applied.
;

save_

